19
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:24,599
Come on, what a sissy.

20
00:02:26,299 --> 00:02:29,699
This place called Tsuzura Ori Pass,

21
00:02:29,699 --> 00:02:33,699
has a succession of 99 curves, big and small in all.

22
00:02:34,999 --> 00:02:38,799
I feel nauseated just listening to you.

23
00:02:38,799 --> 00:02:41,699
Where is Mitsuhiko?

24
00:02:41,699 --> 00:02:45,199
Mitsuhiko's reading a book in the car.

25
00:02:45,199 --> 00:02:47,099
What?

26
00:02:47,099 --> 00:02:48,799
Mitsuhiko!

27
00:02:48,799 --> 00:02:51,499
It feels just great out here!

28
00:02:51,499 --> 00:02:55,099
No, thanks. I'm reading the best part now!

29
00:02:56,799 --> 00:03:00,499
Dr. Agasa, Ai didn't come along again.

30
00:03:02,399 --> 00:03:05,999
Ai was saying she had something to do.

31
00:03:07,899 --> 00:03:10,099
Dr. Agasa, I'll bet you that...

32
00:03:10,099 --> 00:03:11,499
This was what happened,

33
00:03:11,499 --> 00:03:17,099
"I'm not interested in camps."

34
00:03:17,099 --> 00:03:20,599
You're really good, Genta. It's just like her.

35
00:03:20,599 --> 00:03:21,999
Bull's eye.

36
00:03:24,099 --> 00:03:25,099
What's that?

37
00:03:32,499 --> 00:03:33,499
Oh, no!

38
00:03:33,499 --> 00:03:35,399
Dr. Agasa! Get the police and an ambulance!

39
00:03:35,399 --> 00:03:36,599
Okay!

40
00:03:47,599 --> 00:03:52,999
"Great Fall From Mt. Ryujin"

41
00:03:55,099 --> 00:03:58,699
You said you were resting at the scenic spot there

42
00:03:58,699 --> 00:04:01,099
when you witnessed the car go over the cliff,

43
00:04:01,099 --> 00:04:04,199
-so you came running over, right? -Yes.

44
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,899
That dent?

45
00:04:07,699 --> 00:04:09,299
If so...

46
00:04:09,299 --> 00:04:11,499
I'd like to ask you once again...

47
00:04:11,499 --> 00:04:15,099
Did you notice something else suspicious, like a car or a person?

48
00:04:15,099 --> 00:04:17,899
No, nothing at all.

49
00:04:17,899 --> 00:04:19,999
I see.

50
00:04:19,999 --> 00:04:22,199
That's it.

51
00:04:22,199 --> 00:04:23,999
Officer.

52
00:04:24,999 --> 00:04:26,499
What is it, sonny?

53
00:04:26,499 --> 00:04:30,099
May I go and take a look at what the men are doing above?

54
00:04:30,099 --> 00:04:32,799
No, no. It's not something for a child to watch!

55
00:04:32,799 --> 00:04:35,799
I think they're almost finished up there anyway.

56
00:04:35,799 --> 00:04:37,199
It should be okay.

57
00:04:37,199 --> 00:04:38,999
But...

58
00:04:38,999 --> 00:04:40,199
But, sonny,

59
00:04:40,199 --> 00:04:44,399
make sure you don't get in the way of their work when you watch them.

60
00:04:44,399 --> 00:04:46,699
Yes, sir!

61
00:04:50,299 --> 00:04:51,999
Hey, Mitsuhiko,

62
00:04:51,999 --> 00:04:54,199
don't we have to go, too?

63
00:04:55,199 --> 00:04:58,599
Conan's going to go off on his own like always, you know?

64
00:04:58,599 --> 00:05:00,499
Who cares?

65
00:05:00,499 --> 00:05:02,399
Let him do what he pleases.

66
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:05,899
We've got something better here.

67
00:05:05,899 --> 00:05:08,099
Something better?

68
00:05:15,499 --> 00:05:16,899
Okay, here!

69
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:18,399
Okay!

70
00:05:18,399 --> 00:05:22,299
16.33 meters.

71
00:05:22,299 --> 00:05:24,199
16.33...

72
00:05:24,199 --> 00:05:25,799
There.

73
00:05:25,799 --> 00:05:27,399
It's a piece of polish that rubbed off!

74
00:05:27,399 --> 00:05:29,399
Really?

75
00:05:31,699 --> 00:05:34,299
Look, it's dark blue!

76
00:05:34,299 --> 00:05:35,699
Dark blue.

77
00:05:35,699 --> 00:05:37,099
Which means...

78
00:05:37,099 --> 00:05:38,499
Yeah!

79
00:05:40,299 --> 00:05:42,099
So that's what happened.

80
00:05:44,099 --> 00:05:47,299
We came all the way out here to have a picnic

81
00:05:47,299 --> 00:05:50,099
and get messed up in an accident like this.

82
00:05:50,099 --> 00:05:51,999
It's not an accident.

83
00:05:53,199 --> 00:05:55,499
What do you mean it's not an accident?

84
00:05:55,499 --> 00:06:00,699
Didn't the officer there ask you if you saw any other cars?

85
00:06:00,699 --> 00:06:01,999
Yeah.

86
00:06:01,999 --> 00:06:06,999
That car fell over because it was pushed from behind by another car.

87
00:06:06,999 --> 00:06:07,999
What?

88
00:06:07,999 --> 00:06:09,599
That car had a dent in the rear,

89
00:06:09,599 --> 00:06:12,599
an indication of it having been hit from behind.

90
00:06:12,599 --> 00:06:14,499
Besides, the paint that seemed to have rubbed off

91
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:18,099
from the other car was also found.

92
00:06:18,099 --> 00:06:19,099
Moreover,

93
00:06:19,099 --> 00:06:22,899
the car that hit from behind most likely did so deliberately.

94
00:06:22,899 --> 00:06:25,799
Then it's homicide.

95
00:06:25,799 --> 00:06:27,299
Yeah.

96
00:06:27,299 --> 00:06:30,499
Don't we have to cooperate with the police?

97
00:06:30,499 --> 00:06:33,999
It'll be fine, after all, they've got so much evidence.

98
00:06:33,999 --> 00:06:38,599
But, all they've got is rubbed off paint and a dent in the rear.

99
00:06:38,599 --> 00:06:42,099
The Japanese police are usually very efficient.

100
00:06:42,099 --> 00:06:43,999
So long as a piece of rubbed off paint is found,

101
00:06:43,999 --> 00:06:46,999
from the color and substance they can figure out the model of the car, too.

102
00:06:46,999 --> 00:06:49,199
Then all they have to do is go asking around for details

103
00:06:49,199 --> 00:06:50,999
to get to the one who did it.

104
00:06:51,499 --> 00:06:53,699
I see.

105
00:06:55,499 --> 00:06:56,699
Mitsuhiko,

106
00:06:56,699 --> 00:06:58,099
