107
00:06:58,699 --> 00:07:02,499
Quiet. Conan will hear you.

108
00:07:06,899 --> 00:07:09,399
This is it, Genta.

109
00:07:10,399 --> 00:07:11,899
What is this?

110
00:07:11,899 --> 00:07:13,299
It's a code.

111
00:07:13,299 --> 00:07:14,299
A codes?

112
00:07:17,699 --> 00:07:21,699
I picked it up near the site of the accident just a while ago.

113
00:07:22,599 --> 00:07:25,999
Then, shouldn't you have told the police about it?

114
00:07:25,999 --> 00:07:29,199
But, what we saw was just an accident, wasn't it?

115
00:07:29,199 --> 00:07:32,699
It's hard to believe that a code has anything to do with it.

116
00:07:32,699 --> 00:07:33,899
You're right.

117
00:07:33,899 --> 00:07:36,699
Codes are usually used for figuring out

118
00:07:36,699 --> 00:07:38,199
where treasures are hidden, aren't they?

119
00:07:38,199 --> 00:07:40,099
Right, exactly.

120
00:07:40,099 --> 00:07:42,399
Treasure.

121
00:07:42,399 --> 00:07:45,099
So, take a good look at this!

122
00:07:45,099 --> 00:07:49,799
See, on the very top in the square, the equation "100 minus 1" is written.

123
00:07:49,799 --> 00:07:52,299
Okay, Genta, what is 100 minus 1?

124
00:07:53,299 --> 00:07:55,799
Nine...

125
00:07:55,799 --> 00:07:57,599
Ninety-nine?

126
00:07:57,599 --> 00:07:59,299
Right.

127
00:08:00,399 --> 00:08:02,699
Is there something that crosses your mind

128
00:08:02,699 --> 00:08:04,899
when you think of the number 99?

129
00:08:05,899 --> 00:08:08,699
99...

130
00:08:08,699 --> 00:08:10,799
Nine...

131
00:08:10,799 --> 00:08:11,999
911, ambulance.

132
00:08:11,999 --> 00:08:13,699
Nope.

133
00:08:14,699 --> 00:08:19,299
Whatever gave you the idea of 911 at this point?

134
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:21,299
First aid bandage then?

135
00:08:21,299 --> 00:08:23,099
I got it!

136
00:08:23,099 --> 00:08:24,999
It's the Tsuzura Ori Pass, right?

137
00:08:24,999 --> 00:08:26,199
Dr. Agasa just explained

138
00:08:26,199 --> 00:08:29,499
that there is a succession of 99 hairpin curves, didn't he?

139
00:08:29,499 --> 00:08:31,399
Correct.

140
00:08:31,399 --> 00:08:32,999
Which means that this code indicates

141
00:08:32,999 --> 00:08:36,999
a place somewhere in the Tsuzura Ori Pass area.

142
00:08:36,999 --> 00:08:39,699
And, did you figure out where it is, Mitsuhiko?

143
00:08:39,699 --> 00:08:44,299
No, but this code sure looks familiar.

144
00:08:44,299 --> 00:08:46,499
Where did you see it, Mitsuhiko?

145
00:08:48,299 --> 00:08:49,899
Hey, you guys!

146
00:08:50,899 --> 00:08:53,699
What's with all the racket?

147
00:08:53,699 --> 00:08:55,099
It's nothing!

148
00:08:55,099 --> 00:08:57,899
Right, right. We're not talking about any codes.

149
00:08:57,899 --> 00:08:58,999
Codes?

150
00:08:58,999 --> 00:09:03,099
Oh, well, the novel that I was reading you see...

151
00:09:03,099 --> 00:09:04,499
Some codes came out...

152
00:09:04,499 --> 00:09:08,299
They're too easy for you, Conan, so...

153
00:09:08,299 --> 00:09:11,199
Gosh, so it's children's stuff.

154
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:15,799
I've got it.

155
00:09:20,599 --> 00:09:21,799
Okay then, you guys,

156
00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:24,199
Dr. Agasa and I are going fishing,

157
00:09:24,199 --> 00:09:25,799
don't forget to chop the firewood.

158
00:09:25,799 --> 00:09:27,599
Okay...

159
00:09:27,599 --> 00:09:28,899
Bye.

160
00:09:31,099 --> 00:09:33,299
Here goes!

161
00:09:33,299 --> 00:09:36,199
Mitsuhiko, did you really figure it out?

162
00:09:36,199 --> 00:09:38,499
It was in the book that I was reading!

163
00:09:38,499 --> 00:09:39,899
Really?

164
00:09:39,899 --> 00:09:41,999
This!

165
00:09:41,999 --> 00:09:43,699
What is this?

166
00:09:43,699 --> 00:09:45,799
The keyboard of a computer?

167
00:09:45,799 --> 00:09:47,199
Yes.

168
00:09:47,199 --> 00:09:49,699
Numbers are written in numerical order from the top left,

169
00:09:49,699 --> 00:09:53,699
and they correspond to the same hiragana keys!

170
00:09:53,699 --> 00:09:55,999
For instance, 1 and 4 equal the hiragana "ta".

171
00:09:55,999 --> 00:09:58,999
2 and 7 equals "to" and so forth.

172
00:09:58,999 --> 00:09:59,999
All right!

173
00:09:59,999 --> 00:10:02,099
Let's try it!

174
00:10:02,099 --> 00:10:05,599
Genta, please read the number codes.

175
00:10:05,599 --> 00:10:07,199
Okay!

176
00:10:07,199 --> 00:10:10,499
0 and 4, 2 and 3, 3 and 8.

177
00:10:10,499 --> 00:10:12,399
0 and 4 ecuals "u".

178
00:10:12,399 --> 00:10:14,199
2 and 3 equals "se".

179
00:10:14,199 --> 00:10:16,899
3 and 8 equals "tsu".

180
00:10:16,899 --> 00:10:18,899
A right turn?

181
00:10:18,899 --> 00:10:22,499
What is this mark supposed to mean?

182
00:10:24,399 --> 00:10:27,699
Maybe this is the shape of the road?

183
00:10:27,699 --> 00:10:30,199
Right! You're probably right.

184
00:10:30,199 --> 00:10:31,999
That's why the first code can be deciphered as

185
00:10:31,999 --> 00:10:35,099
"Turn right at the intersection".

186
00:10:35,099 --> 00:10:37,699
You're fantastic, Mitsuhiko.

187
00:10:37,699 --> 00:10:38,699
Let's continue.

188
00:10:38,699 --> 00:10:40,399
I'll write it down.

189
00:10:47,299 --> 00:10:48,899
This is boring.

190
00:10:50,799 --> 00:10:52,099
There, it's done!

191
00:10:52,099 --> 00:10:54,599
Please read it.

192
00:10:54,599 --> 00:10:56,199
I'll follow along on the map.

193
00:10:56,199 --> 00:10:57,299
Okay!

194
00:10:57,299 --> 00:11:00,699
Turn right at the intersection after passing Tsuzura Ori Pass.

195
00:11:00,699 --> 00:11:02,799
Turn right at the forked road,

196
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:05,099
then turn left at the next fork.

197
00:11:05,099 --> 00:11:07,299
Cross two bridges,

198
00:11:07,299 --> 00:11:10,299
turn left after the 2nd bridge and goal.

199
00:11:10,299 --> 00:11:12,599
Okay, it's over here.

200
00:11:12,599 --> 00:11:17,099
The pension house is over here, so it's pretty close.

201
00:11:17,099 --> 00:11:18,899
Let's go check it out.

202
00:11:18,899 --> 00:11:20,699
Maybe we'll find the treasure.

203
00:11:20,699 --> 00:11:23,199
I'm sure Conan will be vexed.

204
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:33,199
We're here.

205
00:11:34,699 --> 00:11:37,999
Hey, are you guys upstairs?

206
00:11:37,999 --> 00:11:40,899
We've had a big catch!

207
00:11:41,999 --> 00:11:43,099
What is this?

208
00:11:45,899 --> 00:11:48,199
Hey, bad news.

209
00:11:48,199 --> 00:11:50,599
The kids are nowhere in sight!

210
00:11:50,599 --> 00:11:51,799
What?

211
00:11:59,399 --> 00:12:01,699
Hey, Mitsuhiko.

212
00:12:03,099 --> 00:12:05,799
Are we not there yet?

213
00:12:05,799 --> 00:12:10,399
We've only got a little more to go, so hang in there, Genta.

214
00:12:10,399 --> 00:12:13,899
We're crossing the 2nd bridge now.

215
00:12:13,899 --> 00:12:17,799
After we turn right at the next fork, we'll get there!

216
00:12:17,799 --> 00:12:19,999
We've still got that much more to go.

217
00:12:19,999 --> 00:12:21,999
Hang in there, Genta!

218
00:12:21,999 --> 00:12:24,799
If we find the treasure, you'll get a luxurious serving of eels over rice!

219
00:12:24,799 --> 00:12:26,799
Eels over rice.

220
00:12:26,799 --> 00:12:28,599
Okay, if we find the treasure,

221
00:12:28,599 --> 00:12:30,699
