222
00:12:30,699 --> 00:12:34,099
Let's go, Mitsuhiko, for 100,000 eels over rice.

223
00:12:34,099 --> 00:12:35,999
All right, that's the spirit.

224
00:12:39,099 --> 00:12:41,699
This is bad. Could this be...

225
00:12:42,699 --> 00:12:44,299
Did you figure it out?

226
00:12:44,299 --> 00:12:46,699
Dr. Agasa, call the police right away!

227
00:12:46,699 --> 00:12:47,799
What?

228
00:12:47,799 --> 00:12:49,999
They went to the hideout of the one

229
00:12:49,999 --> 00:12:52,099
who pushed the car over just a while ago.

230
00:12:52,099 --> 00:12:53,899
What?

231
00:12:53,899 --> 00:12:58,399
So this was the code they were talking about in the car a while ago.

232
00:12:58,399 --> 00:12:59,899
Darn!

233
00:13:10,288 --> 00:13:12,888
We did it! We've finally come, Genta!

234
00:13:12,888 --> 00:13:14,188
It's over there!

235
00:13:18,688 --> 00:13:20,588
Hey, Mitsuhiko,

236
00:13:20,588 --> 00:13:22,688
are you sure this is the right place?

237
00:13:22,688 --> 00:13:26,488
It doesn't look to have anything to do with treasure, does it?

238
00:13:26,488 --> 00:13:27,988
What a thing to say!

239
00:13:27,988 --> 00:13:31,788
We came exactly as the code said, so it's got to be right!

240
00:13:31,788 --> 00:13:36,988
Besides, it's places like this that treasures are usually hidden.

241
00:13:36,988 --> 00:13:39,188
Okay, let's go inside then!

242
00:13:46,488 --> 00:13:49,388
Yes, thank you.

243
00:13:50,588 --> 00:13:53,888
The police will rush over to the site immediately.

244
00:13:53,888 --> 00:13:55,988
Let's hurry on over, too.

245
00:13:55,988 --> 00:13:56,988
Okay.

246
00:13:58,388 --> 00:14:00,988
It seems that nobody is in...

247
00:14:00,988 --> 00:14:04,988
Hey, Mitsuhiko, where's the treasure?

248
00:14:11,688 --> 00:14:13,688
The building farthest beyond...

249
00:14:15,088 --> 00:14:16,488
Look!

250
00:14:16,488 --> 00:14:20,288
That building over there is capable of being locked.

251
00:14:20,288 --> 00:14:22,588
-I'm sure it's there. -Yep.

252
00:14:22,588 --> 00:14:24,488
Let's check it out!

253
00:14:32,588 --> 00:14:34,588
This is...

254
00:14:34,588 --> 00:14:36,488
Amazing!

255
00:14:40,688 --> 00:14:43,688
Look at all those foreign model cars!

256
00:14:43,688 --> 00:14:46,088
Hey, Mitsuhiko,

257
00:14:46,088 --> 00:14:48,988
there's no treasure anywhere, though.

258
00:14:50,588 --> 00:14:52,088
Strange.

259
00:14:52,088 --> 00:14:54,588
Hey, you two.

260
00:14:54,588 --> 00:14:56,888
There's something funny about this car.

261
00:14:56,888 --> 00:14:57,888
See.

262
00:14:57,888 --> 00:15:00,588
It has no license plate.

263
00:15:00,588 --> 00:15:02,988
You're right.

264
00:15:02,988 --> 00:15:04,688
Hey, Mitsuhiko.

265
00:15:04,688 --> 00:15:06,788
There's none on this one, too.

266
00:15:07,488 --> 00:15:10,788
Maybe they're all stolen cars.

267
00:15:11,988 --> 00:15:15,888
I'm sure they're planning to sell it off to some foreign country.

268
00:15:15,888 --> 00:15:19,888
We've come to the hideout of car smugglers!

269
00:15:19,888 --> 00:15:21,788
Exactly!

270
00:15:29,888 --> 00:15:33,188
You're the brats that were at the site of the accident...

271
00:15:36,188 --> 00:15:38,288
Who cares!

272
00:15:38,288 --> 00:15:41,688
Where's the guy with the mustache and the other kid?

273
00:15:41,688 --> 00:15:44,088
Just who are you referring to?

274
00:15:44,088 --> 00:15:45,988
Don't you play dumb with me!

275
00:15:47,588 --> 00:15:49,688
What was that sound?

276
00:15:49,688 --> 00:15:51,888
-The sound of gunfire! -What?

277
00:15:51,888 --> 00:15:53,688
Hurry up will you, Dr. Agasa?

278
00:15:53,688 --> 00:15:55,488
All right!

279
00:16:01,488 --> 00:16:03,188
I'll ask you once more.

280
00:16:03,188 --> 00:16:07,588
Where's the guy with 4 the mustache and the other kid?

281
00:16:07,588 --> 00:16:09,888
I have no idea what you're talking about.

282
00:16:09,888 --> 00:16:11,088
What?

283
00:16:11,088 --> 00:16:12,888
Hey, Mitsuhiko.

284
00:16:12,888 --> 00:16:14,688
Mitsuhiko.

285
00:16:14,688 --> 00:16:17,688
No, I can't get Conan and Dr. Agasa involved in something

286
00:16:17,688 --> 00:16:20,288
I got messed up in because of my actions.

287
00:16:21,388 --> 00:16:22,488
He's right.

288
00:16:22,488 --> 00:16:23,688
Yeah.

289
00:16:25,288 --> 00:16:28,088
You must really want to die.

290
00:16:36,388 --> 00:16:38,088
It's me.

291
00:16:38,088 --> 00:16:40,988
Sorry, I've only got 5 for now.

292
00:16:40,988 --> 00:16:44,888
Sada chickened out and rode off with one.

293
00:16:44,888 --> 00:16:47,388
Yeah, I took care of that.

294
00:16:47,388 --> 00:16:49,288
I hit him from behind at the ridge,

295
00:16:49,288 --> 00:16:51,788
and he fell headfirst all the way down.

296
00:16:52,788 --> 00:16:55,188
I'm no goof.

297
00:16:55,188 --> 00:16:57,988
I'll scrap the car before the police get to it.

298
00:16:57,988 --> 00:17:01,588
Once it's scrapped, there's no proof.

299
00:17:05,088 --> 00:17:06,288
That's...

300
00:17:13,088 --> 00:17:14,988
Hey, what's with you guys?

301
00:17:14,988 --> 00:17:16,688
What's with you?

302
00:17:16,688 --> 00:17:19,088
Swinging around a rifle at children!

303
00:17:19,088 --> 00:17:21,388
Dr. Agasa.

304
00:17:21,388 --> 00:17:23,388
You're the one who was at the scene of the accident.

305
00:17:23,388 --> 00:17:25,688
There couldn't be better timing. You saved me time looking for you!

306
00:17:25,688 --> 00:17:27,688
No use, mister.

307
00:17:27,688 --> 00:17:29,488
See, you hear it, don't you?

308
00:17:30,488 --> 00:17:32,388
That police car is headed here.

309
00:17:32,388 --> 00:17:33,888
What?

310
00:17:33,888 --> 00:17:37,188
They're coming here

311
00:17:37,188 --> 00:17:39,888
to arrest you, mister!

312
00:17:39,888 --> 00:17:41,288
What?

313
00:17:44,688 --> 00:17:46,288
All right...

314
00:17:47,888 --> 00:17:50,488
Hey, hey, officers...

315
00:17:50,488 --> 00:17:53,488
I haven't done anything wrong.

316
00:17:53,488 --> 00:17:57,088
Before we hear you out, give us that gun of yours.

317
00:17:57,088 --> 00:17:59,488
Oh, you mean this gun?

318
00:17:59,488 --> 00:18:03,588
I was only trying to scare the kids

319
00:18:03,588 --> 00:18:05,788
because they trespassed on my property.

320
00:18:05,788 --> 00:18:08,088
I see.

321
00:18:08,088 --> 00:18:11,088
By the way, is that your car?

322
00:18:11,088 --> 00:18:13,888
Yeah, that's right. Anything wrong?

323
00:18:13,888 --> 00:18:19,688
Well, a car happened to go over the cliff at Tsuzura Ori Pass

324
00:18:19,688 --> 00:18:22,588
and it seems that a car of the same model as your

325
00:18:22,588 --> 00:18:24,988
pushed that car over from behind.

326
00:18:24,988 --> 00:18:29,088
Your car has a dent too and it looks like to have struck something.

327
00:18:29,088 --> 00:18:32,488
What? Are you suspecting me?

328
00:18:32,488 --> 00:18:35,288
There are several hundreds of cars like this, aren't there?

329
00:18:35,288 --> 00:18:37,388
Just how many of those hundreds do you think

330
00:18:37,388 --> 00:18:40,288
happened to be at the scene of the accident?

331
00:18:40,288 --> 00:18:43,588
And where were you, May I ask, at that time?

332
00:18:43,588 --> 00:18:47,088
Sorry, that was an accident.

333
00:18:47,088 --> 00:18:48,688
Since the scenery was so beautiful,

334
00:18:48,688 --> 00:18:51,488
I took my eyes off the road.

335
00:18:51,488 --> 00:18:53,788
And the next thing I knew, crash!

336
00:18:53,788 --> 00:18:55,188
He's lying, officer!

337
00:18:55,188 --> 00:18:57,288
Shut up, stay out of this, brat!

338
00:18:57,288 --> 00:18:58,388
No, I'm not shutting up!

339
00:18:58,388 --> 00:18:59,788
You just said on the phone

340
00:18:59,788 --> 00:19:02,688
that you struck the car and pushed it over the cliff!

341
00:19:02,688 --> 00:19:04,388
I heard you say so, too!

342
00:19:04,388 --> 00:19:06,088
Me, too!

343
00:19:06,088 --> 00:19:11,188
Hey, officer. Are you going to believe what those brats say?

344
00:19:11,188 --> 00:19:14,188
Just how do you think I can push a car over a cliff

345
00:19:14,188 --> 00:19:15,588
by crashing from behind at a sharp bend like that?

346
00:19:15,588 --> 00:19:16,988
You did exactly that!

347
00:19:16,988 --> 00:19:20,488
You succeeded perfectly!

348
00:19:20,488 --> 00:19:22,788
Old man! Quit your gibberish!

349
00:19:22,788 --> 00:19:24,988
Do you have proof, or what? Proof!

350
00:19:24,988 --> 00:19:26,588
Of course there's proof.

351
00:19:26,588 --> 00:19:29,488
In the foreground of the curve where that car fell over,

352
00:19:29,488 --> 00:19:32,188
there were two pairs of tire marks,

353
00:19:32,188 --> 00:19:36,288
that were left behind when the car was hit from behind.

354
00:19:36,288 --> 00:19:40,388
In other words, you collided twice.

355
00:19:40,388 --> 00:19:42,088
So what?

356
00:19:42,088 --> 00:19:45,688
I wasn't looking at the road and I collided twice.

357
00:19:45,688 --> 00:19:49,688
Well, there is a possibility too, however...

358
00:19:49,688 --> 00:19:55,088
Do you know the space between the tires of the car that fell over?

359
00:19:55,088 --> 00:19:58,588
Yes, 16.33 meters.

360
00:19:58,588 --> 00:20:04,188
And, at what speed were you going at on that road?

361
00:20:05,288 --> 00:20:07,788
Just about 30 kilometers!

362
00:20:07,788 --> 00:20:11,188
Well, I guess so...

363
00:20:11,188 --> 00:20:14,988
The fact that you were going at 30 kilometers means

364
00:20:14,988 --> 00:20:18,388
you were going at about 8.3 meters per second.

365
00:20:18,388 --> 00:20:24,088
In order to leave skid marks at a spacing of 16.33 meters.

366
00:20:24,088 --> 00:20:26,288
It would take you approximately 2 seconds.

367
00:20:26,288 --> 00:20:28,888
After colliding into the car in question, the first time,

368
00:20:28,888 --> 00:20:30,188
for a period of 2 seconds,

369
00:20:30,188 --> 00:20:32,288
you never steered to avoid another collision,

370
00:20:32,288 --> 00:20:34,188
nor did you step on the brakes.

371
00:20:34,188 --> 00:20:36,988
Rather, you collided again!

372
00:20:36,988 --> 00:20:38,288
If this is not called colliding deliberately,

373
00:20:38,288 --> 00:20:39,888
what else would you call it?

374
00:20:40,888 --> 00:20:44,088
So, if you have anything more you want to say,

375
00:20:44,088 --> 00:20:47,088
we'll hear you out at the station.

376
00:20:47,088 --> 00:20:48,388
Darn!

377
00:20:48,388 --> 00:20:50,088
Officer...

378
00:20:51,088 --> 00:20:55,588
There are luxurious cars without license plates in the building beyond.

379
00:20:55,588 --> 00:20:58,588
I'm sure those cars are all stolen cars.

380
00:20:58,588 --> 00:21:01,988
Good work, all of you!

381
00:21:03,088 --> 00:21:04,488
But, listen.

382
00:21:04,488 --> 00:21:07,388
Don't ever do something dangerous like this again!

383
00:21:07,388 --> 00:21:09,788
Yes, sir...

384
00:22:46,088 --> 00:22:49,988
Darn. I just don't seem to have the knack for chopping firewood.

385
00:22:51,088 --> 00:22:52,788
Darn, darn it!

386
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:55,888
Hey, we need more firewood!

387
00:22:55,888 --> 00:23:00,588
Hey, Conan, why don t you help us a bit on this side, too?

388
00:23:00,588 --> 00:23:02,288
No way!

389
00:23:02,288 --> 00:23:04,688
It's your fault for loafing around without chopping firewood

390
00:23:04,688 --> 00:23:08,488
like you should've been, serves you right.

391
00:23:08,488 --> 00:23:10,888
Yes, yes, all right.

392
00:23:10,888 --> 00:23:12,488
One "yes" is enough!

393
00:23:12,488 --> 00:23:13,788
Yes!

394
00:23:13,788 --> 00:23:17,788
I hope they learn their lesson and quit doing dangerous things.

395
00:23:19,488 --> 00:23:22,188
How disappointing, though.

396
00:23:22,188 --> 00:23:23,488
What is?

397
00:23:23,488 --> 00:23:27,788
Conan deciphered that code in no time at all!

398
00:23:27,788 --> 00:23:30,188
You were fantastic too, Mitsuhiko!

399
00:23:30,188 --> 00:23:31,788
Not only did you figure out the code,

400
00:23:31,788 --> 00:23:33,988
you also were right about the smugglers.

401
00:23:33,988 --> 00:23:38,088
Oh, I just thought so because it was in the book I was reading.

402
00:23:38,788 --> 00:23:42,188
Just great. Maybe I should look through it, too.

403
00:23:42,188 --> 00:23:45,688
Oh, I've got just the thing for you, Genta!

404
00:23:45,688 --> 00:23:48,488
"Children's Lunch Murder Case" is the title of it.

405
00:23:48,488 --> 00:23:49,688
What a funny title!

406
00:23:49,688 --> 00:23:53,788
I would rather have eels over nice than a children's lunch.

407
00:23:54,388 --> 00:23:56,888
Hey, haven't you guys learned your lesson or what?

408
00:23:58,688 --> 00:24:00,988
"Next Episode" -How nice and bitter!

409
00:24:00,988 --> 00:24:03,488
This is indeed what you call the world of 'Wabi-Sabi'!

410
00:24:04,388 --> 00:24:07,888
I wonder what's up? Why is she looking around like that?

411
00:24:07,888 --> 00:24:11,188
Are you saying that the master is afraid of a monster?

412
00:24:11,988 --> 00:24:14,488
I wonder if there really is such a thing as a monster?

413
00:24:14,488 --> 00:24:18,088
Don't be ridiculous! No way should such a thing exists!

